title: Russell Wright for Conant Ball Coffee Table in Coral Lacquer
description: Russel Wright for Conant Ball round maple table in the perfect hue of coral lacquer. Perfectly proportioned and elegantly appointed.

title: 1960s Stiffel Venetian Torchiere Floor Lamps - a Pair
description: Slim and regal pair of Venetian inspired torchiers. Brass hardware with hand cut screens and mica shades. A stunning, rare and unique pair of lamps made by Stiffel c. 1967. Weighted base with glorious caste detail. Whether your style is Italian, Gothic, or you want something to illuminate your Arabian Nights, these beautifully made lamps are subtle because of their slim profile, but still have a lot of presence because of the beautifully detailed surfaces. Use to frame a window, sofa or bed. Excellent for minimal, eclectic, period or traditional rooms.

title: 1930s Malian Chi-Wara Head Crests- a Pair
Vintage Chinese Pedestal in Tones of Watery Blues and Greens
description: Vintage Chinese pedestal in watery gradations of blue turquoise to deep forest green. Original finish with Art Deco floral and geometric cutouts. Largerr matching pedestal also available separately.

title: Late 19th Century Dark Academia Table Lamp
description: The perfect adjustable lamp for your study, kunstkammer, laboratory or bedside.  Made from antique lab equipment, these lamps feature solid cast iron construction with an all glass base.  Easily adjustable in height, and direction.  A minimalist style perfect for for modern or historic interiors.  Pair with Dark antiques, or clean modern looks.  Features cloth cord and deco style plugs for a truly unique look. Coordinating lamp available if you need a pair.  A Maison Lobo original design.

title: 1980s Bold Yellow Faux Bamboo Etageres
description: A beautiful pair of Regency or Chinoiserie etageres in a rich brilliant yellow enameled steel. Shelves are removable marbleized porcelain in rich tones of matte white with steel blue to deep charcoal veining. Each shelf board is unique due to the glazing process. Identical shelving is solid with clean welds and unique dual ring appliques that imitate bamboo. A modernist take on a classic design. Can be used as shelving in a living area or positioned bedside. Middle shelf is 29" high while each shelf measures 24.25" w X 12.25" d. Yellow is more egg yolk than canary.

title: 1960s Majolica Seal Point Cat Figurine
description: A beautifully rendered sculpture of a mischievous pampered Siamese Cat.  Perched on a beautiful venetian pillow and adorned by a matching amulet.  Sumptuous colors and fine representation.  Classic Italian Majolica.

title: 1950s Italian Side Chairs- a Pair
description: An extremely elegant pair of modern chairs with original upholstery. Detailed legs are solid hardwood.  A perfect pair of chairs for a small dining table, boudoir or living room.   Made in Italy and imported by Maison Lobo.  A finishing detail for your Gio Ponti inspired room.  Blend seamlessly with Danish Modern and French Art Deco.

title: Mid 20th Century Robsjohn-Gibbings Geometric Side Table
description: The pure geometry of T.H. Robsjohn-Gibbings. A perfect end tables by the master of mid-century design. The interplay of rectilinear lines create the perfect blend of dynamic interplay. Original bleached mahogany finish. Solid vintage condition. Perfect for refinishing in a beautiful lacquer or keep as is.

title: Early 20th Century Japanese Drum Table
description: A wonderfully carved Asian Drum Table / Stool adorned with dragon and cloud motif.  A perfect addition to any room.  Carved mahogany with a beautifully patinated finish and marble top.  Sturdy.  An exceptional example at home in just about any interior.

title: 1950s Paolo Buffa Style Italian Upholstered Chairs - a Pair
description: An iconic pair of Paolo Buffa style Chairs with original floral upholstery.  A beautiful study in geometry,   Perfect in a minimalist or maximalist setting.   Change up the upholstery for a minimal look or leave as is for a cozy maximalist look.  Great structural shape, with some wear consistent with age. Imported directly from Italy.

title: 1950s Robsjohn Gibbings Side Table
description: The perfect geometry of Robsjohn-Gibbings in a blond finish.  A clean, round table that exemplifies pure modernist design.  Coordinating step table also available.  Ready to be refinished, lacquered or matte finished. Brass Widdicomb tag on underside and T.H. Robsjohn-Gibbings stenciling on underside.

title: 1930s Fontana Arte Wall Sconces - a Pair
description: A beautiful pair of wall sconces and brass by masters of lighting Fontana Arte.  Made in Italay c. 1936.   Hand formed brass leaves delicately frame rich peacock blue Murano glass shades.  Ready to hardwire or use how they are with candles.

title: 1970s Brown Saltman Cocktail Table
description: Masculine, geometric table by Brown Saltman.  Perfect for a groovy lodge look or a swinging bachelor pad.   Sophisticated lines, in sturdy materials.  Solid hardwood pecan with channeled leather trim.  Very solid and heavy glamorously thick glass top. Excellent condition.  Matching side table available.

title: Late 19th Century Venetian Dragon Bowls - Set of 4
description: A collection of four Venetian dragon bowls in dazzling gold and green.  Hand made on the island of Murano in the venerable workrooms of Salviati.  These delicate creatures have survived the past century with wings and tongues intact.  A stunning group that can be used as decorative objects or added to your dining table for extra ooomph.  Frilled rims mounted with a unique dragon.

title: 1960s Pair of Tonala Cat Figurines
description: A beautiful pair of large Tonala cats with striking fantasia style painting.  Inquisitive eyes and sweet smiles are the hallmarks of these classic figures.  Made in Jalsisco and hand painted.  One is signed Solis the other is by Ken Edwards.  Both made in the 1960s.  The larger cat has some hairline cracks but is extremely stable.  The smaller cat is perfect.

title: Late 19th Century Double Dragon Krater by Salviati
description: A spectacular 19th c. Murano krater from the venerable workrooms of Salviati.  Beautiful hues of cornflower blue and gold.   Mounted with gold flecked prunts and double dragons.  Intricately crafted wings and delicate red tongues.  A glorious centerpiece for a dining or entry table.   Part of a larger collection of dragon motif glass.

title: Scissor Chairs With Convertible Table, by Michael Van Bueren
description:
A master stroke of Mexican Modernism, at once sculptural and functional. Attributed to Michael Van Bueren.A pitch perfect set of four scissor style lounge chairs in the style of Hans Wegner with an exceptional table that converts from a game table to a coffee table. All four chairs fold for storage. Manufactured and hand built by Austin mfgr. of Mexico City. An intricate and flawless pattern of woven rush adorns this beautifully cherry finished palm wood. No cracks or breaks or splits. Solid cast brass fittings and hardware. A perfect accent to your Palm Springs patio, San Miguel Villa or Midwest Sun Room. Sturdy solid and beautifully finished. Although emulated in many iterations, this set looks to predate the Hans Wegner version. Made between 1940 - 1960 Includes 1 convertible table and 4 chairs.

Table measures 31.5 x 31.5 x 28.5 (game table)  31.5 x 31.5 x 18.5 (drinks table)

Price includes 4 chairs and 1 table

title: 1960s Vintage Syrian Chairs - a Pair
description: A stunning pair of mid-century cock chairs beautifully inlaid with brass filigree.  A rare and exotic treat, made of hardwood and brass.   Perfect for entry or small balcony with ample table surface for teacups, ashtrays or other elegant accoutrement.  Sturdy but mobile.  A

title: Postmodern Wood & Tin Floor Lamp
description: The third in a trio of handcrafted lamps by artist Dan Abramson.  A beautiful lamp with loads of 80s style.  Crafted from wood and tin into a beautiful postmodern composition evocative of Memphis designs.  A warmer version of postmodernism that would blend beautifully with Sottsass and other 80s Italian design. California designed and made.  The tin canopy creates an amazing silhouette and shadow when turned on.

title: Mid-Century Rosewood Sofa
description: Stunning and rare Mid-Century Chinese Settee with auspicious horseshoe style back, and three carved panels feating symbols for wealth, power and prosperity.  Long lean lines perfect in traditionally styled or minimalist room.  Tight joints and comfortable seating area.  We can make a custom cushion upon request.  Three matching chairs available.

title: Art Deco Style Busts by Giá – Lời. - a Pair
description: Beautifully mounted pair of busts by Vietnam artist Gia-Loi c. 1940s.   Cast of copper by  Indochine artist  Giá – Lời.   A stunning accessory for a variety of interiors form Asian Modern to Fantasy to Minimal or Regency.  Each bust is mounted on an lacquered block of solid hardwood.  Substantial weight and a beautiful patina.  Unaltered original condition.

title: Vintage Monumental Brass Candlesticks- a Pair
description: Extra-large Brass candelabra for a major statement.   Perfect for oversize mantels or dramatic dining tables.   Generously sized for large credenzas and high ceilings, or mix scales to create more drama.

title: 1950s Ico Parisi Side Tables
description: Biomorphic end tables in glass and mahogany with brass fittings. A fine example of midcentury Italian design. Lightweight and easily portable.

title: Mid 19th Century English Gilt Mirror
description: A stunning gilt mirrors from an English Manor. Beautiful baroque columns with entwined grape leaves, gilt in original condition with original glass. Beautifully patinated glass in a striking arch frame with extra wide molding. 2 available in shop

title: 1970s Brown Saltman Side Table
description: Masculine, geometric table by Brown Saltman.  Perfect for a groovy lodge look or a swinging bachelor pad.   Sophisticated lines, in sturdy materials.  Solid hardwood pecan with channeled leather trim.  Excellent condition.  Matching Cocktail table available.

title: 1960s Vintage Gondola Chairs by Harvey Prober - a Pair
description: A beautiful pair of Harvey Prober Gondola chairs with original finish. The chairs were updated in the 80s with a wonderfully Memphis inspired pastel cotton print. A great pair of slipper chairs perfectly sized for a modern room.

title: Monumental 19th Century Bodhisaatva Cast Iron Sculptures - Set of 2
description: A beautiful and monumental pair of cast iron Bodhisattva.  Measuring nearly four feet tall each softly featured, resplendent face is adorned with a crown of the three Western Saints.  Bases are hand carved with cutouts to securely cradle and support each bust. An architectural temple or monastery ornament, this superb rendition dates from sometime before 1870.   There is no varnish, chemical treatment nor any other applied finish. A very fine pair that radiates wisdom and compassion.

title: 1980s Lily Table by Arthur Court
description: A beautiful classic 80s transitional design by Arhtur Court. Made of cast aluminum with an extra thick glass top. Perfect as a bedside table, drink table or side table.

title: Sumptuous Mahogany Bar Cabinet
description: Stylish and beautifully proportioned. Art Deco / Art Moderne transitional cabinet with elegant details galore;  including marquetry trim, as well as a harlequin cut glass pattern. Gold mirrored backing provides a soft and glamorous ambient lighting.  Beautifully restored to maintain its original warmth. Imported from Switzerland.  Comes with three keys to keep your items safe and secure.  Room for records or audio equipment make this a perfect cabinet for gentleman's room, office or dining room.

title: 1960s Space Age Stools - a Pair
description: A spectacular pair of biomorphic stools with loads of personality.. Perfect as foot stools, additional seating or as drink tables.  Newly powder-coated in a gleaming white satin finish.  Self-leveling feet have been replaced with identical brass feet from the original manufacturer.  Sturdy construction with clean fresh orange upholstery.

title: Sintesi Terra Floor Lamps by Ernesto Gismondi for Artemide - a Pair
description: Pair of iconic Memphis floor lamps for Artemide. A chic way to introduce postermodernism into your interior.  Styled after vintage microphones with moveable wire grills to protect the bulb.  Foot switch operation with bulbs included.

title: American of Martinsville Mahogany Side Tables - a Pair
description: Light mahogany duplex side tables with polished nicKel drawer pull.  Perfectly scaled for bedside or sofaside.  A muted neutral tone with mellowed yellow wood tones and subtle graining.  Perfect for traditional or more modern interiors.

title: 1980s Papillon Prosim Sedni Postmodern Chair by Bořek Šípek
description: An icon of 80s design. 5 legged Papillon chair by Bořek Šípek. A fabulous melange of matelassé, leather and cherry wood. Postmodernism at its best.

title: 1950s Italian Bar Cart
description: Stunning black bar cart with brass accents. Floating glass panels in an ebonized wood from. Biomorphic details including solid wood handle, tear drop shaped shelves on a steel chassis that runs smoothly and quietly. A rare and gorgeous bar cart, perfect for entertaining or displaying your bottle and glass collections. Imported from Italy.

title: Mid 20th Century Lounge Chair Attributed to Adrian Pearsall
description: Extra wide Barcelona Style lounge chairs with a sled base in walnut.  Generously proportioned seat could seat 2 comfortably.  Original upholstery in excellent condition for its age. Use as is or reupholster.  Generously proportioned for prolonged sitting. Unmarked. Attrib. Adrian Pearsall

title: 1980s Dan Abramson Postmodernist Bar Cabinet
description: California Design meets Post Modernism in this beautiful two piece cabinet / altar, handcrafted  from recycled wood in the 1980s with polychromed finish by Artist Dan Abramson.  Long and lean this cabinet is perfect for tight spaces with enough pizzaz to carry a large expanse of wall. bold coloration and wavy details.  A quintessential California artist with Santa Monica roots.  We can add glass shelving and or an RIFD lock to secure your fine wine or liquor collection. Use as a bar, hat storage, entry storage or as a nicho for an altar.

title: Masque Lamps by Giocometti Bros.
description: Masque lamps by Alberto Giocometti c. 1940. Original wiring, no shades. Pair available, sold separately.

title: Mid-Century Rosewood Chair
description: A stunning trio of three Mid-Century lounge chairs with auspicious horseshoe style back and carved splats.  Made from rosewood with a beautifully restored finish.  Bentwood splats feature celestial carvings of clouds, scrolling tracery and dragons.   Buy one or all three.  Matching sofa available.   An excellent chair alone or stunning as  suite in a your formal living room.  Sturdy well made.

title: Mid 20th Century Pair of Chinese Garden Stools
description: A beautiful pair of Chinese export garden stools c. 1950s.  Beautiful shades of blue from midnight to purple.  Spectacular muted mottled finish.  Sold as a pair.  Perfect tables or seating.  No chips or crackling.

title: Perfectly Sculpted Art Nuevo Chaise
description: Art Nouveau Bentwood Chaise Lounge with perfect caning..  Brass plaque indicating Gruau Barcelona an old Hotel.  A perfect sculpture for your entry or curated living space.  An exceptional and comfortable example of timeless Art Neuvo elegance with whiplash curves and organic tendrils.  Works well with a Gitane or boho aesthetic as well as more design focused and minimal spaces.

title: Wood & Metal Ziggurat Floor Lamp
description: Architectural floor lam in wood and metal by Santa Monica artist Dan Abramson.  A beautiful marriage of art and craft is apparent in this beautiful Memphis inspired postmodern floor lamp.  Standing a whopping 84 inches, this beautiful lamp evokes a beautiful sunrise.  A ziggurat shaped base proves a sturdy base.  Canopy made of repurposed tin panels.

title: Andrew Delfino Caned Venetian Settee
description: Highly carved Bench / Sofa by SF designer Andrew Delfino, c. Cane back and seat. Hand carved c. 1960 Sofa has been recaned and has no damage. A stunning piece of furniture, quality through and through. Generous length perfect for a grand entry, a cozy nook, sunroom or covered loggia.

title: Mid 19th Century English Gilt Mirror
description: A stunning gilt mirrors from an English Manor. Beautiful baroque columns with entwined grape leaves, gilt in original condition with original glass. Beautifully patinated glass in a striking arch frame with extra wide molding. 2 available in shop

title: Late 20th Century Architectural Wall Mount Console
description: A genius wall mount console design by Santa Monica artist Dan Abramson.   Made from a repurposed window frame, this sturdy wall console mounts easily with two screws.  Perfect as a plant display under a window, an entry table, bedside table or anywhere you need additional surface area.  Geometric base gives an architectural sophistication to this well thought out design.  Combine with other Dan Abramson pieces for a truly unique and charming garden / plant room.

title: Morrisson Cartier Table Lamp
description: Incredibly rare Modernist table lamp in bronze with faceted jewel shade consisting of 40 pieces of cut glass.  Manufactured and designed by Morrison Lighting c. 1980

title: 1980s Dan Abramson Postmodern Light and Lyrical Wall Console
description: A master stroke in architectural woodwork.  A wood and polychrome wall console that doesn't take itself too seriously.  Designed and built by Santa Monica artist Dan Abramson.  Easily wall mounts with two screws.  Very sturdy and stable.  Perfect as a sideboard, bar, plant display or entry console.  A wonderful piece that will easily adapt to a multitude of situations.

title: Postmodern Metal & Wood Lamp
description: One of a beautiful trio of handcrafted lamps by artist Dan Abramson.  80s postmodernism as exemplified by the koooky craftsmanship of one of Santa Monica's favorite designers.  Art meets craft in this long and lean work of art.  Lighting with style.

title: Satelite Style Floor Lamp
description: Satelite style floor lamp with 6 radiating bulbs in a stunning patinated bronze finish, custom made by Casella, c.  1970s  (15" diameter with bulbs)

title: 1950s Carl Auböck Live Edge Biomorphic Tables - a Pair
description:
A beautiful pair of Auböck tables in his indelible Haute Alpes style. Brought from Switzerland exclusively for Maison Lobo. Use in tandem or end to end when length matters. The perfect table for a Napa inspired retreat or a Chalet modern effect. So evocative of Zermat or Les Arcs, The perfect blend of nature and nurture in live edge Austrian Yew with stealthy Iron legs. 

Table A: 52.25 W x 16.5 D x 12.75 H
Table B: 48.75 W x 12.75 D x 12.75 H

title: Vintage Modernist Italian Stool in the Style of Carlo Scarpa
description: A trio of beautifully restored stools in the manner of Carlo Scarpa.  Manufactured by venerated Italian workshops of ISA International.  A pedestal base supported by four steel openwork arms that seem to levitate on highly polished, caste brass adjustable feet.  Upholstered in a textured, mossy green fabric to the original specifications.  Perfectly at home in any Carlo Scarpa structure. Amply filled cushions for a comfortable seat.  Use as occasional seating, bunch together and use as a coffee table.

title: 1980s Verner Panton Reinterpreted Side Chair
description: A Panton classic reinterpreted in fabric by Thayer Coggin.  Upholstered in a damask, but would look incredible reinterpreted in velvet.
